Description: PULIDIKI Car Cleaning Gel Car Cleaning Putty Kit Slime Cleaner Interior Auto Detail Tools Supplies Car Accessories Stocking Stuffers Gifts for Men Women White Elephant Gifts for Adults Teens Christmas
Review: I pruchased this to use in my vehicle to get into those hard to clean areas. I ended up using it in my dad's work truck to really put it to the test. He is working in a very dusty area with the red dirt....his truck was covered in the thick dust, so a perfect test of the product. He and I cleaned what we could with rags, but I wanted to try this stuff out on the creases and vents. It worked alright. Here are the pros/cons of the product from my initial test:Pros:- Ease of use: This is very easy to use. Just open it up, pull it out, and start dabbing it into the dusty areas. I found that tapping the dust to get the worst of it off before dragging it over a second time worked best.- Cleaning: This is good for loose dust. It worked really well at removing the dust in the vents and some of the corners you could not get a rag into.Cons:- Cleaning: This did not remove some of the stuck on dust that a rag would have removed. I also found that getting in tighter crevices did not work very well either. It also left a little greasy feel that may attract dust or that some people may not like on their dashes or inside their vehicles.- Cleaning the product: With as heavy of dust that was in my dad's truck, the gel got pretty dirty. I am not sure the best way to clean it, or if you can even clean it. Rags and towels are easy...just throw them into a washing machine. I'm guessing this is use until completely dirty and throw away.- Messy: This also leaves a greasy feel to your hands. With rags, you can usually minimize this, but this stuff gets all over your fingers, especially the finger you use to press it into vents.Overall, this is something that is a neat idea, but it really is not great. It worked okay at getting loose dirt and dust off of surfaces, but you could also get the same results from using something like tape or wrapping a small tool with some cloth and using cleaning agents. This might make a cheap, fun stocking stuffer if you want to get something that is different. Personally, I don't think I'll buy this again and just use rags.

Review: I would love to give this 5-stars, and I would if I were only reviewing its performance.Overall, this product does exactly what is says it will do. The quality is good, its sturdy, and the carrying pouch is just OK (Hate the pouch).However, the battery leads are too short for some applications.If you are connecting this to a battery with easy access you are golden. One of the uses I have is to occasionally jump start a 5K generator and the battery is not easily accessible. Do not misunderstand me, I can connect the cables from this unit to the generator battery terminals. But the cable is so short it is difficult to plug the cable into the jump starter.  What I end up doing is first connect the cable to the battery, then get the jump starter close enough to plug the cable into it. Next comes a little balancing act, as if I do not hold it in place the cable will drop out of the jump starter.I have a few NOCO products, and they all work well. Big fan!But come on NOCO, for applications like mine the short cable is infuriating. An extra couple of inches of cable would make this jump starter perfect.Last thing:Battery Cable - Too shortJump Starter - works great, compact, easily stored, ruggedStorage Bag - Hate it! will be putting into a small caseMy Use Cases - Jump Generator, Jump Started a 2022 Chevy Truck with 5.7L V-8, Jump Started stranded car

Description: REDTIGER Dash Cam Front Rear, 4K/2.5K Full HD Dash Camera for Cars, Included 32GB Card, Built-in Wi-Fi GPS, 3.16” IPS Screen, Night Vision, 170°Wide Angle, WDR, 24H Parking Mode(F7NP)
Review: We purchased the F7N Redtiger camera about 18 months ago and it has now paid for itself 100x over when it provided evidence to the police and insurance that my wife was not the one at fault in an accident that totaled her vehicle and the other party lied to the police.  My wife was going to get the ticket after the officer talked to the other party first, but she was able to show the officer the cam video and they reversed course and issued the ticket to the other party.  Then the other party lied to their insurance, but after providing the video to their insurance, the adjuster immediately accepted 100% responsibility.Easy to install and with clearly written English instructions.  Great suction cup with integrated GPS antenna makes installation a breeze.  Cam will slide off mount if you want to hide it while parked without removing the entire mount.  Crystal clear video, front at 4k and back at 2k, produce high resolution video where you can read license plates and even identify who was driving another vehicle.Even more importantly, it has a good app that you can use to directly download video from the cam without pulling the card and taking it to a computer.  Just in case you are in an accident, you can instantly download the relevant video to your phone and show to Law Enforcement and e-mail to your insurance company.  This is hugely important so a ticket can be issued to the at-fault party on scene as my wife did.  If you can't show the officer when writing the report, they may issue the ticket to the wrong party or no one if they can't figure out who was at fault.  If this happens, it's a long up-hill battle to get the other party's insurance to pay out and the police will never cancel an incorrectly issued ticket, so it forces you to go to court to defend yourself.  If you are in a serious accident (if anyone goes to the hospital, it's serious), the officer may confiscate the SD card or even the whole camera for evidence.  You may not get it back for weeks or even months.  Sometimes they get lost an then you have nothing.  Have a copy safely on your phone so you can give it to your insurance company and lawyer immediately!Buy the REDTIGER F7N Dash Cam Hardwire Kit to go with it if you want 24/7 monitoring without killing your car battery.  Never wonder who backed into you in a parking lot or keyed your car if it happens to you.Some things that set Redtiger apart from the others:They actually have tech support.  We had an issue with one camera not liking our SD card and contacted support to see if we had a bum Cam or bad setting as the issue was intermittent.  Turns out it was just a faulty card after running a write test on the computer.  Not a big issue as SD cards are cheap, but good to know that if you have an issue that Redtiger does support what they sell.Software updates.  We've owned the F7N for about 18 months and have received software updates to improve functionality.  The cam was great when we got it and even better now with new features added.Proof in the pudding:We liked our F7N so much we just bought another Redtiger cam, a F7N Touch, for a new (to us) vehicle and it's great too.Note:  I wasn't paid for this review nor given a demo unit or anything else.  I'm only a satisfied customer that is enjoying the premium quality and features at a great price vs the big-name competitors and their high prices.

Description: REDTIGER Dash Cam Front Rear, 4K/2.5K Full HD Dash Camera for Cars, Included 32GB Card, Built-in Wi-Fi GPS, 3.16” IPS Screen, Night Vision, 170°Wide Angle, WDR, 24H Parking Mode(F7NP)
Review: Received the F7N TOUCH Dash-Cam on 11/6/24 and installed it on 11/7/24. I am very pleased with this dash-cam.Here are some of the features that I am really pleased with so far:TOUCH SCREEN: Makes it easy to navigate and select the different features programmed in this dash-cam.VOICE CONTROL: Makes it easy to access and control the various features of this dash-cam. I especially like that you can just say “Turn on WiFi” and the cam will activate the WiFi. The camera powers on automatically once you turn on your vehicle and when you use the voice control and say “Turn on WiFi”, wait until you see “WiFi Connected” on the dash-cam and the camera will then connect automatically to the mobile app as well.REDTIGER MOBILE APP: The mobile app feature is extremely helpful and user friendly. You can control many of the dash-cam’s features through the mobile app including, but not limited to, switching the dash-cam’s front/rear/split screen views.CAMERA CLARITY: The front and rear camera’s offer crystal clear views.INSTALLATION: Installation is not difficult. I was actually up for the challenge of installing this myself. Included with the dash-cam is a plastic crowbar/spatula type tool for installing/running the two provided cables (power cable and rear camera cable). The tool allows you to run the cables through the windshield’s front top edges of the vehicle headliner and along the interior rubber window trim, as well as inserting the cables through the vehicles interior plastic pillars. I ran the power cable through the right side of the headliner and rubber trim, and ran the rear camera cable on the left side of the headliner, rubber trim and interior plastic pillars. I was able to achieve clean and professional results in my installation.WORD TO THE WISE: Heed the warning in the manual. Be sure to turn the dash-cam on ONLY after you have connected both the front AND rear cameras. DO NOT turn the camera on otherwise until BOTH camera’s are connected.CONCLUSION: The F7N TOUCH Dash-Cam is a very, very good product. REDTIGER’s customer service is also attentive, courteous and responsive. I highly recommend this product to anyone looking for a dash-cam that is easy to install, user friendly, reliable, and offers many features.

Description: AstroAI Tire Inflator Portable Air Compressor Tire Air Pump for Car Tires - Car Accessories, 12V DC Auto Pump with Digital Pressure Gauge, Emergency LED Light for Bicycle, Balloons, Yellow
Review: I've had a Slime Home Air Station (120 volt only) for many years, but the hose recently failed and couldn't be repaired, so it was time to find a replacement. This piece meets the need. It seems well-made and comes with a useful User Manual. However, it IS quite different from what I had before.First off, it's 12 volt only, via a standard auto 12V  socket. The User Manual said to start the car's engine while using it, so I'm guessing it draws a fair amount of current and might flatten your battery with prolonged use. The inflator hose is also much shorter than what I was used to, but still long enough to reach the valve-stem at the 12 o'clock position while the compressor remains on the ground. It's a bonus that it stays put when it's running and doesn't skate across the surface, as my old unit did.The built-in digital pressure gauge is easy to read, but reads about 2.5 PSI over actual pressure as checked by a separate calibrated  pressure gauge. Actual 35 PSI reads 37.5 PSI on this unit. Not really a big deal. If you can make change, you can do the math.The best feature is the Auto-stop at a preset pressure. My old unit did not have this, so I had to stare at the gauge for several minutes as the needle slowly crept up the dial. On this one, just set the desired pressure and start the compressor. The digital pressure gauge shows inflation progress 0.5 PSI at a time. When it hits the preset setting, it shuts off within a few seconds. My car has 235/55ZR20 tires and this unit will raise the pressure from 32 PSI to 38 PSI in about 3 minutes; not as fast as having a tank-type 120 volt 150 PSI compressor, but certainly acceptable for an occasional-use compact 12 volt unit. I paid less than $30 for this one with next day delivery, so I think qualifies as a great value. Highly recommended.

The pressure indicator seems accurate, which is a critical feature when inflating tires.Pros:Lightweight and compact design makes it easy to store and handle.Long cord provides excellent reach, especially for larger vehicles like a Jeep.Accurate pressure indicator for reliable readings.Cons:The connector occasionally slips out of the cigarette lighter socket during use, which can be a bit annoying.After about 10 minutes of use, the connector and hose become quite hot, which might raise durability concerns with prolonged operation.Real-world performance:I tested the compressor on my Jeep's 225/65R17 tires, inflating them from 19 PSI to 35 PSI. Each tire took about 4–5 minutes to inflate. After an off-road trip, it took approximately 20 minutes to restore all four tires to road-ready pressure. While this isn't lightning-fast, it’s efficient enough for the occasional off-road enthusiast.Overall:This compressor is a solid choice for light to moderate use, especially for off-roaders or anyone needing a portable option. A few minor issues aside, it gets the job done reliably.

Description: NOCO GENIUS1, 1A Smart Car Battery Charger, 6V and 12V Automotive Charger, Battery Maintainer, Trickle Charger, Float Charger and Desulfator for Motorcycle, ATV, Lithium and Deep Cycle Batteries
Review: I have a truck that mostly sits in the garage. Every time I need to back it out of the garage, the battery is dead.I know that just sitting isn't good for batteries, not to mention this battery is several years old.Now keep in mind, this is a large amp battery for a SUV, which was so dead, a turn of the key and I didn't even get lights on the dash. I stuck this little charger on it and it took a day and a half, but it charged completely. Ok, now I'm beginning to get a tad impressed.I have two of those old type chargers, you know the ones that after a while you can hear the acid boiling inside the battery, and the battery is getting really hot... you know the chargers that tell you not to leave it on your battery for any extended period of time as this might (will) damage the battery (possibly even start a fire). Well... no more.I'm a total convert now to using smart chargers, and this one seems especially good. I really hope I don't find some little something that breaks 6 months from now, cause I really like this charger! It seems very well designed and made and most of all, it works great.The only negative I can find, it has a single button to select one of several charging modes, and LED's to indicate which option you have chosen,  and those LED's are pretty much self explanatory, as well as an advanced mode where you have to push and hold the single button to enter advanced charging mode. For example, if your battery is so bad, the charger cannot detect there is even a battery hooked up, you can tell it to go ahead and start charging anyway which is a really nice feature. As another reviewer mentioned, when you need to use some of the more advanced functions, if you've lost the booklet, well... good luck. The multi-language booklet briefly explains all of the options, what the LED's mean, and that's pretty much it, verbose it isn't..It comes in a really nice packaging, like you're really getting something ( and you are), the unit itself seems well made and thought out, you would think a bit more of an effort would have been put into the manual.But, perhaps the product speaks for itself... and it does. And, after all most users will hook it up to their 12 volt car/boat/motorcyle battery, plug it in, select the regular 12v battery option, and that's all most will ever need. Once the battery is charged completely, the charger senses that, and switches automatically to just maintaining the battery. If you loose power while charging (or maintaining), this charger just picks up right where it left off, so there is no worries about pushing buttons or selecting modes, it knows what you were doing before, and starts right back up with doing it again.Am I glad I got it:  YesWould I buy it again: Yes.

Review: I am using this for a trickle charger on a car that is not driven very often. The battery was constantly getting discharged due to normal non-driving drain (electronic devices: remote sensors, clock, alarm system, etc.). The charger appears to be well made and works well. I chose this charger based on some external reviews on chargers. Description: NOCO GENIUS1, 1A Smart Car Battery Charger, 6V and 12V Automotive Charger, Battery Maintainer, Trickle Charger, Float Charger and Desulfator for Motorcycle, ATV, Lithium and Deep Cycle Batteries
Review: I use this charger to charge and maintain my batteries in my tractor and motorcycle. I also have to charge both lead/acid and lithium ion batteries. This battery does both, and claims to recondition the lead batteries and keep the lithium ion batteries at peak performance. I’ll see if the second claim is true after a few cycles on both battery types.I can tell you my tractor battery is over a year old, and took longer than my old charger normally took to charge it. I ran the tractor all day yesterday vacuuming leaves on my 2 acre wooded lot, and it never once had difficulty starting. This is unusual, because my PTO drains it slowly while my deck is running, and my battery was starting to show its age.Yesterday I had no problem starting my tractor, and when I finished and hooked it up to the charger to top it off, the charger turned green before I went in the house. What had taken almost 1-1/2 hours when I first charged it, took about 10 minutes this time. I can only assume the new charger was reconditioning my battery the first time, but won’t know until I start my tractor again today.I didn’t leave the charger on my tractor to trickle charge. I brought it in to charge my lithium ion motorcycle battery since I’ve been neglecting it for my tractor’s battery.First; it recognized the battery type automatically, took a second to start charging, and within 30 to 45 minutes had charged it to 100%. Very easy and fast. I probably hadn’t charged it for over a month because I was using it exclusively for my tractor. As most people know; lithium ion batteries hold their charge for a long time. It started my Honda with no sluggishness, but that also is normal for lithium ion batteries.I would like the charger display to be larger and show different charging levels, but its size won’t let that happen. You can’t put 10lb of crap in a 5lb bag.So far this charger has met or exceeded my expectations. It certainly is better than my other charger, and if it does rehabilitate my lead/acid battery as claimed I’m certainly going to buy a second one for my shed.

Whether I'm navigating through busy city streets or cruising on the highway, my phone remains securely in place, minimizing vibrations and ensuring clear visibility of the screen. Additionally, while the suction cup is robust, occasional cleaning and reapplication may be necessary to maintain optimal grip, especially in extreme temperatures.Conclusion:In conclusion, the Qifutan Car Phone Holder is a commendable choice for anyone looking to enhance their driving experience with a reliable and versatile phone mount. Review: I’m probably like you, and figured, yeah, they say it’s going to do all these great things and it’ll probably not work anywhere near as advertised. Oh boy was I wrong about that.This product is quite frankly amazing. It’s very easy to use and doesn’t take hours and hours. Everything you need is in the kit except masking tape, which I would highly recommend you use to tape off the perimeter of your light so you don’t get any of the coating on your car paint or accidentally hit it with the sand paper.You first use the oxidizer remover, wipe and clean that off, then you go to the 1000 and 2000 grit sanding discs. Get a good spray bottle with nice clean water, keep the headlight wet while you’re sanding it because basically what you’re doing is wet sanding the surface. You can actually feel the sandpaper, engaging the scratches, and when you finally have a nice smooth, feel to it, spray it down and wipe it off and clean it with a microfiber cloth. Then apply the coating. When you apply the coating, it is literally a miracle. How perfect and clean and clear the lens becomes. It looks brand freaking new!I literally was walking around the garage looking at it saying “damn that looks good“, damn that looks good! You will not be disappointed. This is one of the best products to come around in a long, long time and is worth every penny. I even had a little extra left over and did my cub cadet headlight cover.

Older files are overwritten only when the memory card is full, except for locked or emergency recordings, which are preserved.User-Friendly Design:Setting up the dash cam was straightforward, with clear instructions included. While it could benefit from Wi-Fi connectivity and additional cable management tools, these are minor issues compared to the overall value it provides.If you’re looking for a dependable dash cam that offers great performance and protects you in any driving situation, the SUVCON 3-Channel Dash Cam is a smart choice.
